WESTSIDE DIGEST: WEST HOLLYWOOD; 
CIVIC CENTER CONTRACTS 
The City Council has awarded contracts for design, construction and management 
of the new civic center. Gruen Associates was chosen from among 300 applicants 
for the design contract, said Mark Winogrand, director of city development. CRS 
Sirenne of Los Angeles was awarded the construction contract, and John S. Given 
was named the project manager. 
The two companies and Given have been working with the city on construction of 
the new center for more than three months, Winogrand said. 
The $23-million center, which will be in West Hollywood Park, will include City 
Hall, a park, a library and a fire station. Construction is expected to begin 
in May of next year. 
